 extends this Callable[String] and also implements Serializable. The Single Abstract Method (SAM) method erases to `Object call()`, while the lambda should return a `String`. I think I may need a classloader resource for the lambda class. Under the JVM, I can use `c.getClass.getClassLoader.getResourceAsStream(resource)`, possibly calling the lambda class by its name, including a slash.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NpbE7DpnBoog3H8lq1qig5XF|fc_0f86c62bcc67044e0169fb15e409288190b2343c4fb212e70a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/com.typesafe.akka/akka-actor_2.13/2.6.21/src/test/scala/com_typesafe_akka/akka_actor_2_13/LineNumbersTest.scala"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2288, "output": 1298, "cacheRead": 17408, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20994, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778062802193, "responseId": "resp_0f86c62bcc67044e0169fb15d2f4908190adbccb7febb46e8d"}}
